Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7925: replace zero-length array with flexible-array member
Git-commit: 8ad8b8c2dc87fc3d34921330827914c7f2d74466
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc1
References: bsc#1254315

The current codebase makes use of the zero-length array language
extension to the C90 standard, but the preferred mechanism to declare
variable-length types such as these ones is a flexible array member[1],
introduced in C99:

struct foo {
	int stuff;
	struct boo array[];
};

By making use of the mechanism above, we will get a compiler warning
in case the flexible array does not occur last, which is beneficial
to cultivate a high-quality code.[2]

This issue was found with the help of Coccinelle.

[1] https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Zero-Length.html
[2] commit 76497732932f ("cxgb3/l2t: Fix undefined behaviour")

